          "year": 2020,
          "note": "Amanda saw it at Sundance over a year earlier and told Sean to skip it; a rewatch changed her mind on plenty, but not the ending. They spend most of the segment on the tonal whiplash between the film's candy-colored revenge fantasy and its grim subject matter, plus the Variety review that Carey Mulligan publicly objected to and that got the critic, Dennis Harvey, cut loose."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
