        {
          "title": "Da 5 Bloods",
          "year": 2020,
          "note": "His fourth film with Spike Lee and their first in 25 years. Lindo pushed back on his character Paul being written as an explicit Trump supporter; Lee thought it over and told him no, Paul needed to stay Trumpian."
        },
        {
          "title": "Malcolm X",
          "year": 1992,
          "note": "The audition that started the collaboration: Lindo flew to L.A. to read for West Indian Archie and Lee wasn't even in the room, so he had a second audition arranged in New York."
        },
        {
          "title": "Crooklyn",
          "year": 1994,
          "note": "Took a beating on release for not looking like a typical Spike Lee film; Lindo says it's since become a mainstay."
        },
        {
          "title": "Capernaum",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "His answer to the show's closing question about the last great thing he's seen. He called Danny Glover, one of the film's producers, just to ask how the director got that performance out of a toddler."
